## Phase 4 — Silver: structure, extract, spatialise

```
Read AGENTS.md first. We are on Phase 4. Phases 0–3 are green.

Operating rules: work this phase only, then run the checkpoint and STOP. No
destructive commands without asking. Everything under Unity Catalog. Use the
bundle. Verify uncertain CLI/schema details against `databricks bundle schema`.

Build the silver layer in src/pipelines/ and wire it into resources/jobs.yml as a
`silver_transform` job:
  1. AI extraction: use ai_query/ai_extract to turn the free-text description,
     capability, equipment, procedure fields into typed capability flags
     (does_csection, has_icu, obstetric_services, plus any clearly supported
     others), each with a confidence score. Store in mdp.silver.facility_claims.
     These are CLAIMS, not facts.
  2. Build a Vector Search index over description/capability/equipment.
  3. Clean enrichment: deduplicate mdp.bronze.pincode to district grain BEFORE
     any join; snake_case the NFHS columns; map '*' to NULL (never 0); flag
     parenthesised small-sample estimates as low-confidence.
  4. Spatial assignment: assign each facility to a district via
     ST_Contains(polygon, ST_Point(lon,lat)); flag rows missing coordinates as
     geo_inferred = true. Do NOT drop them.
Then `databricks bundle run silver_transform -t dev`.

CHECKPOINT 4 — report all of these with output:
  - Extraction quality: print 30 random facilities with their extracted flags so
    I can hand-label; we need >= ~80% agreement before continuing.
  - No fan-out: silver facility row count is still ~10,000 after joins.
  - Geocoding coverage: report % geo_inferred; confirm those rows are flagged.
  - Vector index status is ONLINE and returns sensible neighbours for a test query.
STOP and report.
```

