## Phase 5 — Gold: unified facility + district desert score

```
Read AGENTS.md first. We are on Phase 5. Phase 4 is green.

Same operating rules: this phase only, checkpoint then STOP, no destructive
commands without asking, Unity Catalog + bundle.

Build the gold layer (gold_build job in resources/jobs.yml):
  1. mdp.gold.facility — one row per facility: facility_id, district_id,
     capability flags + per-flag confidence, geo_inferred, evidence_ref
     (pointer to source record + the exact claim sentence).
  2. mdp.gold.district_desert — one row per district with verified_coverage,
     burden_score, accessibility_score, desert_score, and the counts behind each.
     Use the desert-score formula and weights from AGENTS.md. verified_coverage
     counts ONLY facilities whose relevant capability is verified.
  3. Add data-quality expectations / SQL tests in tests/ that fail loudly on
     NULL desert scores or fan-out.
Then `databricks bundle run gold_build -t dev`.

CHECKPOINT 5 — report:
  - Face validity: list the 5 worst-desert districts; I will sanity-check them
    against known high-burden NFHS-5 districts.
  - Confirm coverage uses verified facilities only (show the join logic).
  - DQ expectations/tests pass; no NULL desert scores where data exists.
STOP and report.
```

