## Phase 6 — Agents (Agent Bricks Supervisor + specialists)

```
Read AGENTS.md first. We are on Phase 6. Phase 5 is green.

Same operating rules. This is the agentic core — go in this sub-order and treat
each as its own mini-checkpoint:

  1. Genie Space over mdp.gold.* — confirm it answers natural-language count
     questions correctly.
  2. Register the geo + desert-score logic as Unity Catalog functions the agent
     can call (mdp.gold.fn_*).
  3. Capability-verification agent (mdp_verify_agent): author with the MLflow
     ResponsesAgent interface; it uses Vector Search + AI classification and
     returns a credibility judgement + confidence for "can facility X do
     service Y?". Log and register it in Unity Catalog.
  4. Supervisor Agent (Agent Bricks): connect Genie + mdp_verify_agent + the UC
     functions + Foundation Model API web search + MCP enrichment. No hard-coded
     routing — steer with instructions.

Install SDKs with uv: mlflow>=3.1.3, databricks-agents>=1.1.0, databricks-sdk.
Prefer deploying the agent on Databricks Apps (Phase 8); a Model Serving endpoint
is fine for interim testing.

CHECKPOINT 6 — report:
  - MLflow eval on a ~15-pair golden Q&A set meets the threshold we set.
  - Trace for "where to deploy a maternal unit in Bihar?" shows the supervisor
    calling Genie + geo tools + verify agent in a sensible order.
  - Verification precision: spot-check 20 claim judgements; low false-positive rate.
  - All agents and functions registered in Unity Catalog with correct grants.
STOP and report.
```

