## Phase 8.5 — Voice & multilingual layer (OPTIONAL)

```
Read AGENTS.md first. We are on Phase 8.5, which is OPTIONAL. Only proceed if
Phase 8 is fully green and we have real time left. If Phase 8 is not solid, say
so and stop — do not start this.

Same operating rules. This is a convenience layer over the existing text demo,
NOT a new capability. Do not modify the supervisor agent or the data spine.

Tier 1 scope only:
  - Voice input: capture mic audio in the app, transcribe via a Whisper Large V3
    Model Serving endpoint OR OpenAI STT routed through AI Gateway. Feed the
    resulting text to the EXISTING supervisor agent.
  - Multilingual: run ai_translate on the transcript (e.g. Hindi -> English)
    before the agent, and translate the answer back for display/playback.
  - Voice output: TTS reads the answer.
  - OUT OF SCOPE: real-time conversational voice (WebRTC/barge-in/turn-taking)
    and any video. Do not build these.

Honesty rule (non-negotiable): the spoken/displayed answer must still state the
confidence and the key caveat. The map + evidence drawer remain the source of
truth. Governance: store transcripts (not raw audio unless required) in Lakebase
under Unity Catalog with a short retention window; document this.

CHECKPOINT 8.5 — report:
  - Spoken English question -> correct transcript -> same ranked answer as typing.
  - Spoken Hindi (or regional) question -> correct district result.
  - Spoken/displayed answer still states confidence + key caveat.
  - No regression: the text-only demo path still works unchanged.
  - Audio/transcript handling is governed and documented.
STOP and report.
```

